  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "Of course, they could not break in because the iron shutters kept them out, but I remember seeing my mother with a kitchen knife.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "It was a, a terrible sight, and I knew something was terribly wrong.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] My brother went to, to yeshiva after his bar mitzvah and I, I longed to go also.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "I was the middle child and I was a girl, and of course that wasn't allowed for me to do.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "I always wanted to be a scholar and I was somewhat of, of a tomboy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "But, because I could not go to study more, I developed my athletic abilities.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "And, in school I became the President of the Athletic Club and the Literary Club.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "It gave me a lot of status and a lot of good feeling about myself.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "So, in spite of the, the environment, which was so negative and which was so harmful, I had a lot of positives coming to me through my efforts at school and through the friends that I enjoyed.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The-- when I was born, I was born with a dislocated hip and I was told to exercise a lot when that was put in place.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And, so I went to ice skating and all kinds of other activities.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "The rabbi of our congregation did not like that, that I mingled so freely with other children, especially with those that were not observant or they were not Jewish and, told my mother not to allow me.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "And I remember my mother standing up for me and saying to, to the religious authority, in these decisions, I have to decide, and that she has to do the exercises, therefore, she will be going.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
